Response

Response is responsible for sending HTTP responses back to a client.

The class takes into consideration the many generic responses HTTP has ranging from 200 to 500, and helps make it easy to output the correct response with headers.

Example:

//Init the class
Response::init();

//Successful Response
Response::createResponse(200, 'Hello Word!');

//Page Not Found
Response::createResponse(404, 'The page you are looking for cannot be found');

array
